**Title: Sr. Business Intelligence (BI) Specialist**

 **Location: 100% Remote**

 **Duration: 12+ Months**



 **Job Description:**
* Promotes the utilization of technical services to resolve business issues within the enterprise, agency, program area, or division;
* Provides technical support on complex business intelligence projects and performs as a Subject Matter Expert in business or functional area;
* May participate in strategic planning processes for ODA's Data Visualization/Business Intelligence team; Assists with developing technical standards and policies to meet the needs of customers, peers, and management;
* Recommends and facilitates quality improvement efforts;
* May serve as a project leader providing guidance, advice, supervision and/or training to other analysts;
* Establishes and maintains strategic partnerships with data visualization-based agencies to help them meet their business and technical needs;
* Collaborates with Data Science/Public HealthGeographics, Data Engineering, Data Management, Data Surveillance, Outreach& Equity, and Data Governance teams within ODA;
* Participates in the Business Intelligence Center of Excellence steering committee as it relates to data governance and visualization best practices;
* Assists Data Visualization/Business Intelligence team with dashboard development as needed.
* The job description is not designed to cover or contain a comprehensive listing of activities, duties or responsibilities that are required of the employee.
* Other duties, responsibilities and activities may change or be assigned at any time

**Skills:**
* Tableau, Power BI, SAS/R, Excel for data visualizations
* SAS/R, Python, etc. for data cleaning and automations
* Demonstrated experience with data manipulation, including cleansing, standardizing, and transforming;
* Specific and extensive knowledge of statistical software, open-source programming languages, and database querying;
* Experience in leading workshops or training sessions;
* Exceptional analytical, conceptual, and problem-solving abilities;
* Advanced knowledge of the application of software engineering process tools;
* Advanced knowledge of project management theories and practices and the ability to apply that knowledge
* Ability to use logic and critical thinking to address issues efficiently and effectively;
* Ability to understand the implications of new information for both current and future problemsolving and decision-making;
* Familiarity with using and interpreting data structures and relationships;
* Ability to understand how change management methodology aligns with and enhances project management and implementation;
* Effectively communicate both orally and in writing.
* Possess at minimum a bachelor's degree with 2+ years of experience (related certifications, trainings, professional work and/or coursework)



